metadata.name: Behind the lens
metadata.description:
Photography has a unique way to change your perspective and narrow your focus. 

Reality takes on a different shape when viewed through the eyes of your lens. 

Hours turn into minutes in long shooting sessions in nature, and, occassionaly, you are gifted with a special moment of insight and clarity that turn into a beautiful shot.

This was one of them. 

Taken in the High Sierra of Bejar in Spain.
